Late Tony Momoh Prince Tony Momoh is dead. Prince Momoh was a veteran journalist, lawyer, politician and former Minister of Information and Culture (1986–1990) during the military regime of General Ibrahim Babangida. He was also the Pro-Chancellor and Chairman, Governing Council of the University of Jos. His last major public intervention was an interview with Vanguard, published in the Saturday Vanguard of January 30. In January 2011, he became the National Chairman of the defunct Congress for Progressive Change CPC, one of the “legacy parties” which merged to form the now ruling All Progressives Congress, APC. READ ALSO: Edo 2020: Tony Momoh reacts to Obaseki’s disqualification from APC primary Known for his bluntness, Prince Momoh was one individual who was committed to any cause he believed in irrespective of whose ox was gored. In that interview with, he said money spent on elected officers was enough to develop Nigeria.